-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, Komercni Banka Move in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-06T14:48:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/czech-stocks-komercni-banka-new-world-resources-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
gained for a third day, rising 0.8 percent to 881.20 at the
close of trading in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   slid 0.8 percent to 365.90
koruna, snapping two days of gains. The Austrian lender had its
long-term debt rating cut two notches to A3 at Moody’s Investors
Service today.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)  , Societe Generale SA’s Czech
unit, climbed for a fourth day, its longest stretch of gains in
three months. The stock advanced 2.4 percent to 3,221 koruna.
Lenders were among the biggest European stock gainers on
speculation policy makers will step up economic stimulus.  To contact the reporter on this story:
